'''= An inalienable right is a right that may not be ceded or transferred away even with  the consent of the holders of the right. Any contract to alienate such a right would be an inherently invalid contract, and, vice-versa, a right such that any contract to alienate it was inherently invalid would thus be an inalienable right.''' [http://www.blog.ellerman.org/2010/03/inalienable-rights-part-i-the-basic-argument-2/]


